    "body": "Unlike on other devices, when a checklist item is toggled, the app scrolls to where the cursor is.\r\n\r\n### Expected\r\nTo keep the app exactly view exactly where I'm working on (toggling on/off a certain checklist item). This is the behavior on iOS, web, and MacOS.\r\n\r\n### Observed\r\nIf you\r\n<!--\r\n***(Required)*** Add a concise description of what you observed.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Reproduced\r\n1. Create a checklist with more items than your screen can visualize\r\n2. Keep the cursor on one of the items that are outside your viewport\r\n3. Go back to the top of the list\r\n4. Toggle on/off one of the first items\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1136160/107046940-fefa1880-67a5-11eb-9936-6adb5d704e49.mp4\r\n\r\nUser info:\r\n\r\nDevice Make: Google\r\nDevice Model: Google Pixel 3a (sargo)\r\nAndroid Version: 11.0.0\r\nSimplenote Version: Simplenote 2.16-rc-2\r\n\r\nAlso reproduced on my Moto E6 with Simplenote 2.15.\r\n\r\nReport: 3708476-zen",
